@dev Returns the key-value pair stored at position `index` in the map. O(1).

devdoc.details: Library for managing an enumerable variant of Solidity's https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/types.html#mapping-types[`mapping`] bytes32 to bytes type. This is a fork of the EnumerableMap from OpenZeppelin Maps have the following properties: - Entries are added, removed, and checked for existence in constant time (O(1)). - Entries are enumerated in O(n). No guarantees are made on the ordering. ``` contract Example {     // Add the library methods     using EnumerableMapBytes for EnumerableMapBytes.Bytes32ToBytesMap;     // Declare a set state variable     EnumerableMapBytes.Bytes32ToBytesMap private myMap; } ``` Maps of type `bytes32 -> bytes32` (`Bytes32ToBytesMap`) are supported.
